# ABYA Ecosystem Environment Configuration Example
# 
# This file serves as a comprehensive template for all environment variables
# required by the ABYA Ecosystem Web3 Learning Management System.
#
# USAGE INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to .env for development: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Copy this file to .env.prod for production: cp .env.example .env.prod
# 3. Update the values with your specific configuration
# 4. Never commit real API keys or private keys to version control
#
# SECURITY NOTES:
# - Use Docker secrets for sensitive data in production
# - Rotate API keys regularly
# - Use different keys for different environments
# - Test all configurations in staging before production

# =============================================================================
# ENVIRONMENT SELECTION
# =============================================================================
# Environment type - affects logging, debugging, and security settings
# Options: development, staging, production
NODE_ENV=development

# Application version and build information
APP_VERSION=1.0.0
BUILD_DATE=
VCS_REF=

